lements as those of   Matthew  , but in reverse order. This is the name of several characters in the Bible, most notably a son of King Saul, who was a devoted friend and supporter of the young David, even when David and Saul were themselves at loggerheads (1 Samuel 31; 2 Samuel 1:19–26). The name is often taken as symbolic of steadfast friendship and loyalty. Well-known bearers of the name include the Irish clergyman and writer  Jonathan Swift  (  1667-1745 ), British theatre director  Jonathan Miller  (  b. 1934 ), British actor  Jonathan Pryce  (  b. 1947 ), and British television presenter  Jonathan Ross  (  b. 1960 )."]},{"name":"Jonn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jon   or  <b>John</b> ."]},{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Mac Con MacNamara was born in 1240, in Ireland, his father, Lochlain Macnamara, was 40 and his mother, Honora O Conor, was 30. He married Mary O Brien in 1265, in Ireland. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"       1240–":"1240–Surnud","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","1242–Female":"1242–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1200":"1200","1265":"1265","1210":"1210","1242":"1242","       1240":"1240","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","       1270":"1270","Ireland":"Iirimaa"},"fi":{"       1240–":"1240–Kuollut","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","1242–Female":"1242–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1200":"1200","1265":"1265","1210":"1210","1242":"1242","       1240":"1240","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","       1270":"1270","Ireland":"Irlanti"},"fr":{"       1240–":"1240–Décédé","1240–Male":"1240–Décédé","1242–Female":"1242–Décédée","1270–Male":"1270–Décédé","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1210–Female":"1210–Décédée","1200":"1200","1265":"1265","1210":"1210","1242":"1242","       1240":"1240","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","       1270":"1270","Ireland":"